Detect Organism

Supports organism detection from genome build or Ensembl identifier.

detectOrganism(object, ...)

# S4 method for character
detectOrganism(object)

Arguments

object

Object.
...

Additional arguments.

Value

Full latin scientific organism name.

See also

Other Gene Annotation Utilities: annotable, gene2symbolFromGTF, gene2symbol, symbol2gene, tx2geneFromGTF, tx2gene

Examples

# H. sapiens
detectOrganism("GRCh38")
#>          human 
#> "Homo sapiens" 
detectOrganism("hg38")
#>          human 
#> "Homo sapiens" 
detectOrganism("ENSG00000000003")
#>          human 
#> "Homo sapiens" 
detectOrganism("human")
#>          human 
#> "Homo sapiens" 
detectOrganism("hsapiens")
#>          human 
#> "Homo sapiens" 
detectOrganism("Homo sapiens")
#>          human 
#> "Homo sapiens" 

# M. musculus
detectOrganism("GRCm38")
#>          mouse 
#> "Mus musculus" 
detectOrganism("mm10")
#>          mouse 
#> "Mus musculus" 
detectOrganism("ENSMUSG00000002459")
#>          mouse 
#> "Mus musculus" 

# C. elegans
detectOrganism("WBcel235")
#>                roundworm 
#> "Caenorhabditis elegans" 
detectOrganism("ce11")
#>                roundworm 
#> "Caenorhabditis elegans" 
detectOrganism("WBGene00000001")
#>                roundworm 
#> "Caenorhabditis elegans" 

# D. melanogaster
detectOrganism("BDGP6")
#>                  fruitfly 
#> "Drosophila melanogaster" 
detectOrganism("dm6")
#>                  fruitfly 
#> "Drosophila melanogaster" 
detectOrganism("FBgn0000003")
#>                  fruitfly 
#> "Drosophila melanogaster"
